<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4489416>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 8–14. Epiphragma gracilistylus Alexander, 1933. 8 – habitus (male); 9 – wings (upper one with less developed wing marking, lower one with well-developed wing marking); 10 – male genitalia in dorsal view; 11 – interbase in dorsal view; 12 – female abdominal sternite 8 and hypogynial valve in ventral view; 13 – furca in dorsal view; 14 – female abdominal sternite 10 in ventral view. Scale bars = 5 mm (8), 2 mm (9), 0.25 mm (10–14)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4489416/files/figure.png" .

